{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3d9f2074-98d5-4fe8-82ea-856de9f12b3b","content":"In your project file, simply **remove** (or delete) the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>   <!-- remove this line -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nMSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform by default**, so removing that property is all you need.\n\n### Key differences after switching\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dotnet test` | Works | Still works |\n| Run directly | No | `./YourTest.exe` works |\n| CLI flags | `--filter` | `--filter` (same), plus `--help` on the exe for platform-specific options |\n\n### Watch out for\n- **VSTest-specific `.runsettings` features** — some may need adjustment; the platform has its own extension model.\n- **Custom VSTest adapters/loggers** — replace with Microsoft.Testing.Platform extensions if applicable.\n- **CI pipelines** — `dotnet test` still works, but if you were invoking `vstest.console.exe` directly, switch to `dotnet test` or the built-in executable.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"78d4b0a2-7e10-4086-9761-d90171c547c7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration, not a codebase-specific task.\n\nHere's what they need to change:\n\n1. Remove `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` from their project file (or set it to `false`). MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0 defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not set to `true`.\n\n2. That's essentially it for the basic switch. But there are some nuances:\n\n\n- The test runner gets built directly into the test project itself, so you can either run tests with `dotnet test` or execute the test executable directly.\n- Some VSTest-specific adapters or settings might need adjusting depending on their setup.","outputTokens":560},"id":"cd3f1182-4b06-4a2a-89a8-edbbe760c8f4","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:52.412Z","parentId":"cf2c967e-9b30-4df4-a708-5ef74ddd461f"}
